,"Final menstrual period before age 45","Final menstrual period before age 50","Final menstrual period between ages 40-45","Final menstrual period between ages 45-50"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EEarly menopause, also known as premature ovarian insufficiency, is defined as the \u003Cstrong\u003Efinal menstrual period before age 40\u003C/strong\u003E. This occurs in approximately 1% of women.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efinal menstrual period before age 45\u003C/strong\u003E is considered early menopause by some definitions, but the strict definition uses age 40 as the cut-off. \u003Cstrong\u003EFinal menstrual period before age 50\u003C/strong\u003E would include both early and normal menopause cases. A \u003Cstrong\u003Efinal menstrual period between ages 40-45\u003C/strong\u003E is considered earlier than average but not technically early menopause. A \u003Cstrong\u003Efinal menstrual period between ages 45-50\u003C/strong\u003E falls within the normal age range for menopause.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENatural menopause typically occurs between ages 45-55, with a median age of 51 years in developed countries. Women who experience early menopause are at increased risk of osteoporosis and cardiovascular disease due to prolonged oestrogen deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early menopause (premature ovarian insufficiency) occurs when the final menstrual period happens before age 40.","Natural menopause typically occurs between ages 45-55, with a median age of 51 years.","The perimenopause is the transitional period of irregular cycles before the final menstrual period."],"references":["Okeke T, Anyaehie U, Ezenyeaku C. Premature menopause. Ann Med Health Sci Res. 2013 Jan;3(1):90-5. doi: 10.4103/2141-9248.109458. PMID: 23634337; PMCID: PMC3634232.","Magraith K, Jang C. Management of menopause. Aust Prescr. 2023 Oct;46(3):48-53. doi: 10.18773/austprescr.2023.014. PMID: 38053812; PMCID: PMC10665088.","Santoro N, Epperson CN, Mathews SB. Menopausal Symptoms and Their Management. Endocrinol Metab Clin North Am. 2015 Sep;44(3):497-515. doi: 10.1016/j.ecl.2015.05.001. PMID: 26316239; PMCID: PMC4890704.","Hawkins SM, Matzuk MM. The menstrual cycle: basic biology. Ann N Y Acad Sci. 2008;1135:10-8. doi: 10.1196/annals.1429.018. PMID: 18574203; PMCID: PMC2913133","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47706"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15696"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47706","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47706"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T14:34:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-17T14:34:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8387"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62260"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emed